Bailey Pulls out of Sydney Athletics Meet Due to Injury
CANBERRA , February 27 ( Xinhua ) -- World record holder for men 's 100 meters Donovan BAiley has withdrawn from Saturday 's track and field meet in Sydney due to a bruised heel .
On Wednesday , Bailey was beaten into third place behind world champion Maurice Greene and Jon Drummond at the Melbourne Grand Prix meet .
Greene clocked the fastest time on Australian soil in running 10.06 seconds into a 1.6 meter per second headwind in Melbourne .
Greene said if there was no headwind he could have the chance of breaking BAiley 's world record of 9.84 .
" I would love to break the world record in Sydney , I would love that , " Greene said .
